## Context Loading (MANDATORY)
When starting a session:
1. Read `00_System/01_context/business-context.md` (L0 — Business Context)
2. Read `00_System/01_context/domain-context.md` (L1 — Domain Context)
3. When working on a specific project, read `[workspace]/00_context/project-context.md` (L2)
4. For feature-level work, ask user for `feature-context.md` if available (L3 — optional, user-managed)

## Gene Flow Rules
- L0 (business-context.md) is IMMUTABLE — never override
- L1 (domain-context.md) must not conflict with L0
- L2 (project-context.md) adds delta context only
- L3 (feature-context.md) is user-managed — read on request, never auto-generate
- Always trace compliance: L3 → L2 → L1 → L0

## System Resources
When working in a Workspace Manager project, the following resources
are available under 00_System/:

- 00_System/01_context/   — Business context (L0), Domain context (L1)
- 00_System/02_policies/    — Unit/Department policies (may be empty)
- 00_System/03_prompts/   — Unit/Department shared prompts (may be empty)
- 00_System/04_standards/ — Architecture standards per Unit (ai/cloud)
- 00_System/05_tool-configs/ — Unit/Department tool configurations (may be empty)

Rules:
1. ALWAYS check the relevant resource before making decisions.
2. Standards files must be followed for architecture and output formatting.
3. When a project workspace is active, read its project-context.md.
4. Folders may be empty (.gitkeep) — skip empty folders silently.

